popid_355949496="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">File Open dialog box<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">The following options allow you to specify which file to open:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">File Name<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Type or select the filename you want to open. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Drives<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Select the drive in which SYNOPSYS stores the file that you want to open. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Directories<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_NormalIndent\"><span class=\"f_NormalIndent\">Select the directory in which SYNOPSYS stores the file that you want to open.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading2\"><span class=\"f_heading2\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Network...<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_NormalIndent\"><span class=\"f_NormalIndent\">Choose this button to connect to a network location, assigning it a new drive letter. <\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_356240511="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">File Save As dialog box<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">The following options allow you to specify the name and location of the lens you’re about to save:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">File Name<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Type a new filename to save a lens with a different name. &nbsp;A filename can contain up to 86 characters and an extension of up to three characters. &nbsp;SYNOPSYS adds the extension .RLE<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">Drives<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Select the drive in which you want to store the lens.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\" style=\"margin: 0px 0px 8px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">Directories<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Select the directory in which you want to store the lens.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_416974317X="<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Print dialog box<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">The following options allow you to specify how the document should be printed:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Printer<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">This is the active printer and printer connection. &nbsp;Choose the Setup option to change the printer and printer connection.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Setup<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Displays a <\/span><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"return hmshowPopup(event, popid_1080641666X, this);\" class=\"popuplink\">Print Setup dialog box<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">, so &nbsp;you can select a printer and printer connection.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Copies<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Specify the number of copies you want to print.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Print Quality<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Select the quality of the printing. &nbsp;Generally, lower quality printing takes less time to produce.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_475574312="<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Print Progress Dialog<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">The Printing dialog box is shown during the time that SYNOPSYS is sending output to the printer.  <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">To abort printing, choose Cancel.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1080641666X="<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Print Setup dialog box<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">The following options allow you to select the destination printer and its connection.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Printer<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Select the printer you want to use. &nbsp;Choose the Default Printer; or choose the Specific Printer option and select one of the current installed printers shown in the box. &nbsp;You install printers and configure ports using the Windows Control Panel. <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Orientation<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Choose Portrait or Landscape.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Paper Size<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Select the size of paper that the document is to be printed on.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Paper Source<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Some printers offer multiple trays for different paper sources. &nbsp;Specify the tray here.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Options<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Displays a dialog box where you can make additional choices about printing, specific to the type of printer you have selected.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Network...<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Choose this button to connect to a network location, assigning it a new drive letter.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_704395037X="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">No Help Available<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">No help is available for this message box.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1727888157X="<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Print Preview toolbar<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">The print preview toolbar offers you the following options:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Print<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Bring up the print dialog box, to start a print job.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Zoom In<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Take a closer look at the printed page.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Zoom Out<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Take a larger look at the printed page.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 4px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold;\">Close<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Normal-1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Return from print preview to the editing window.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_Normal-1\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1412180="<p class=\"p_mine\"><span class=\"f_mine\" style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\">SYNOPSYS User’s Manual<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_mine\"><span class=\"f_mine\" style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;\">Appendix A<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_mine\"><span class=\"f_mine\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_mine\" style=\"border-color: #000000; border-style: solid; border-width: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-left: none; margin: 0px 0px 1px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_mine\" style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase;\">Common File Listing &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<\/span><span class=\"f_mine\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um.htm#um_contents\" class=\"topiclink\">TOC<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_mine\"><span class=\"f_mine\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_mine\"><span class=\"f_mine\">(This section is no longer used.)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span style=\"width:48px\">&nbsp;<\/span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"f_Normal-2\" style=\"font-size: 11pt; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um.htm#um_contents\" class=\"topiclink\">TOC<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_Normal-2\" style=\"font-size: 11pt;\"> <\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_16285102X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><\/p>\n\r<p><\/p>\n\r<p><\/p>\n\r<p><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Alternate Configuration Selection Buttons<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking these buttons changes the current configuration to the number on the button. There are six configurations available, and operations on one are independent of operations on any of the others. The main use of these configurations is for <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um1072.htm#acon\" class=\"topiclink\">multiconfiguration<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> optimization, where variables from one may be picked up by any of the others. This is convenient for when, say, a given objective lens is to be used with several eyepieces, or a lens changes its focal length by inserting and removing elements.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">You may also change the current configuration with the command<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span style=\"width:48px\">&nbsp;<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">ACON <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">NB<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Where <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">NB<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> is a number from one to six.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_16057741X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Annotation editor button:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Click this button to open a toolbar where you can add text, lines, circles, and arrows to your picture.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_681174932X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">AI Off Button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Use this button <\/span><img src=\"aion.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"aion\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> (or the command <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">INT<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">) to turn off AI mode.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">The <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"umch15.htm#ai\" class=\"topiclink\">artificial intelligence<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> feature is one of the most innovative and powerful features of SYNOPSYS, but while new users are becoming familiar with the commands and operation of the program it is sometimes best to turn it off. &nbsp;You can always turn it back on with the command <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">AI<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">, or the button <\/span><img src=\"aion.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"aion\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">. &nbsp;Otherwise, when you make typing mistakes or misspell a command, the AI program will try to interpret what you have typed as though it were an English sentence -- which it very likely is not. &nbsp;Then it will offer you the opportunity to <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-style: italic;\">correct<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> your sentence by retyping the first four characters of a ‘word’ that it cannot understand. &nbsp;You can simply press the &lt;Return&gt; key to get out of this mode. &nbsp;Or you can turn AI off if you are not yet ready to use it.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_15841270X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">AI On button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Use this button <\/span><img src=\"aion.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"aion\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> (or the command <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">AI<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">) to turn on AI mode.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">The <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"umch15.htm#ai\" class=\"topiclink\">artificial intelligence<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> feature is one of the most innovative and powerful features of SYNOPSYS. &nbsp;You will often perform common tasks with AI more quickly than in any other way: for example, you can query or change lens data with sentences such as “4 RD?” or “RAD 4 = 34.66”. &nbsp;And tasks like “PLOT DEFOCUS FOR WAVELENGTH = .4 TO .8” &nbsp;are more cumbersome if done with command language input. &nbsp;See <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"umch15.htm#ai\" class=\"topiclink\">AI<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> for a complete description of this powerful tool.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_662748007X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">ANNEAL button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button opens a dialog where you can enter a desired temperature and cooling rate for a <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um1012.htm#anneal\" class=\"topiclink\">simulated-annealing<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> optimization run.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_648735348X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Arrow Cursor<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button <\/span><img src=\"arrow.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"arrow\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> changes the cursor to the default arrow.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1637010236X="<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Options<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Dialog Text Window<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Prompt When Full<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">When selected, displays a box when the <\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-family: Helv; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"commandwindow.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">Command<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"commandwindow.htm\" class=\"topiclink\"> Window<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\"> buffer becomes full, prompting for user action.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_12176598X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">New Graphics Window button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button opens a new graphics window, which is then available for the next picture that you make. &nbsp;This is intended for when you have selected <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"hid_options_reusewindow.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">Options | Graphics | Reuse Graphics Window<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">, but want to save the current picture.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1592434685="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Copy Screen to Bitmap button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">When you click this button, the program creates a bitmap of the active area of the open window, and sends it to the Windows clipboard. &nbsp;Then you can simply paste it into any third-party software that can accept graphics, such as Word, Corel Draw, and all graphics editor programs -- which can then change it to a jpg file, or any of many other kinds.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1844720310="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Close MACros button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">You should never have to use this button. &nbsp;It is there only for the rare instance when a MACro does not complete properly, usually because of an error condition, and the program leaves the file open. &nbsp;Then, when you try to modify and run the MACro again, you get a file-sharing violation and cannot save it.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Just click on this menu item, and the program will close the open MACro file.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_744721543X="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Context Help command <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading2\"><img src=\"curhelp.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"curhelp\" style=\"float:left;margin:0px 0px 0px 0px; border:none\"><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use the Context Help command to obtain help on some portion of SYNOPSYS. &nbsp;When you choose the Toolbar’s Context Help button, the mouse pointer will change to an arrow and question mark. &nbsp;Then click somewhere in the SYNOPSYS window, such as another Toolbar button. &nbsp;The Help topic will be shown for the item you clicked.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Shortcut<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading2\"><span class=\"f_heading2\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Keys: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;SHIFT+F1<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_812025962="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Copy command (Edit menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to copy selected data from the MACro editor onto the clipboard. &nbsp;This command is unavailable if there are no data currently selected.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Copying data to the clipboard replaces the contents previously stored there.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">Shortcuts<\/span><\/p>\n\r<div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\">Keys:<\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\">CTRL+C<\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r"
popid_180881335X="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Cut command (Edit menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to remove the currently selected data from the MACro editor and put it on the clipboard. &nbsp;This command is unavailable if there are no data currently selected.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Cutting data to the clipboard replaces the contents previously stored there.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">Shortcuts<\/span><\/p>\n\r<div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\">Keys:<\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\">CTRL+X<\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_417589662X="<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">MACro<\/span><span style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span style=\"font-family: Helv; font-weight: bold;\">Open a New Editor with a MAC file<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">Prompts for a .MAC file name, then opens a new MACro editor window. &nbsp;See <\/span><span style=\"font-family: Helv; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"macros.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">MACros<\/a><\/span><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\"> for a general discussion of MACros and their use.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Shortcut:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><img src=\"editmacro.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"editmacro\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><\/p>\n\r"
popid_170212993="<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">MACro<\/span><span style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Create a New Editor Window<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">Opens a new MACro editor window. &nbsp;See <\/span><span style=\"font-family: Helv; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"macros.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">MACros<\/a><\/span><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\"> for a general discussion of MACros and their use.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_600714666="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Paste command (Edit menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to insert a copy of the clipboard contents at the insertion point. &nbsp;This command is unavailable if the clipboard is empty.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">Shortcuts<\/span><\/p>\n\r<div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\">Keys:<\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\">CTRL+V<\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r"
popid_813454713="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Undo\/Can’t Undo command (Edit menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to reverse the last editing action, if possible. &nbsp; The name of the command changes, depending on what the last action was. &nbsp;The Undo command changes to Can’t Undo on the menu if you cannot reverse your last action.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">Shortcuts<\/span><\/p>\n\r<div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\">Keys:<\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\">CTRL+Z or &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;This works when editing text<\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\"><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\">ALT-BACKSPACE<\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\">&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\"><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\">CTRL+U &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;This will undo changes to the lens (not text) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r"
popid_137496989="<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Compress MACro Button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>Clicking this button will cause all blank lines to be deleted from the current MACro. &nbsp;This is intended for when you copy and paste the lines of the MACro from another source, such as the Help file. &nbsp;Depending on the format of the source, the pasted results may contain extra blank lines, which you probably do not want.<\/p>\n\r"
popid_297906228X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Rayset Definition<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\">Clicking this button in the MACro editor will open the <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"hidd_momstandard.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">MOM<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\"> Standard Rayset dialog, where you can define the raysets you want in your merit function. &nbsp;When you click OK in that dialog the rayset parameters you selected will automatically be pasted into the MACro at the current cursor position.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_2131188586="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Ready-made Raysets<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button opens a dialog where you may select from a set of ready-made ray definitions. &nbsp;These can be useful in a variety of situations, and you can very quickly add the required lines to your optimization MACro. &nbsp;Just be sure that the cursor is within the <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um103.htm#aant\" class=\"topiclink\">AANT<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> section before you click this button. &nbsp;For more information, click <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"hidd_momreadymade.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">here<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_151975280="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Edge-definition Wizard Button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Click here to open the <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"hidd_edgewizard.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">Edge- Wizard dialog<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">. This will let you create and edit the edge definition parameters used to define the diameter, bevel, face, and angles that are applied to lens edges by many of the graphics features, including DWG, PER, RPER, ELD, and PAD\/D. Switch 39 must be ON for these edges to appear.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_774068360X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">ERROR button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button turns red when the system encounters an <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um1315.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">error condition<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">. &nbsp;Then you can click here to display all of the unread messages. &nbsp;Most error messages are <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-style: italic;\">not<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> shown on the Command Window, to avoid having the same message show up countless times, especially during optimization. &nbsp;But you can make them appear there as well, if you turn on switch 54.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">You can also display errors with the command<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\" style=\"text-indent: 48px;\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">ERRORS<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">and clear all of the current pending errors with<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\" style=\"text-indent: 48px;\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">ERRORS CLEAR<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_56019323="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Fix Ray Failures<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button only becomes active when you have tried to run the optimization program but it aborted on the first pass because one of the rays called for in the merit function failed to trace. &nbsp;This occurs because a ray missed a surface entirely (MCS error) or encountered total internal reflection (TIR error).<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">When you click this button, the program tries to adjust the lens so that the offending ray will trace through, and then automatically reruns the optimization MACro. &nbsp;For more information, see <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um10312.htm#fix\" class=\"topiclink\">Section 10.3.1.2<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_2037457725X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet: Fold Here<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button <\/span><img src=\"wsfold.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"wsfold\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> will prompt for an angle and direction, and then will insert a fold mirror and a dummy surface for coordinate rotation at the next place where you click in an airspace. &nbsp;An angle of zero degrees folds the light directly back on itself, while 90 degrees is a right-angle fold. &nbsp;You can determine which way to fold most easily by looking at the circled surface numbers on the PAD drawing: these are normally at the +Y edge of the surface.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">You can easily change the sign of the tilt angle later with the button <\/span><img src=\"mflip.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"mflip\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">, and you can adjust the tilt angle value with the slider normally used for CV.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Caution is advised if your system is already folded elsewhere; if you click in a large airspace, the program attempts to determine between which two surfaces you have clicked -- and the click point may sometimes actually be nearer to the vertex of a different surface entirely. &nbsp;In this case, the fold mirror will not go where you intended. &nbsp;The solution is 1) to click close to a desired vertex (you can slide the mirror into its desired location later), and 2) be sure to make a checkpoint before you use this button.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Caution is also advised if you insert a fold mirror before surface 1. &nbsp;If the object is at infinity, this works well enough – although the lens drawings are oriented in the coordinate system of the (new) surface 1, which is of course at an angle, which you probably don’t want. &nbsp;But if the object is finite, the value of TH0 and YMP1 must also change, and the program does not do that for you. &nbsp;The moral is, if you want to insert a fold mirror in front of your lens, add a dummy surface there first (and adjust the object if necessary) and then insert the fold mirror in the space following the new surface 1.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">If you plane to insert a fold mirror just before the start of a ZFILE zoom group, it is also wise to first insert a dummy surface at the desired location. &nbsp;The program by default automatically assigns the inserted surface as part of that zoom group (which is how <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um1017.htm#aei\" class=\"topiclink\">AEI<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> can add elements to a group) -- but in this case you probably don\'t want the mirror to be included. &nbsp;So, after you insert the dummy surface, edit the zoom parameters to remove that surface from the group that follows it, and then fold at that dummy surface.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">You can also fold a system in command mode. &nbsp;See <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um519.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">FOLD<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_85254917="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Freeze Command Window<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button freezes the Command Window. &nbsp;You can do anything with it except read from or write to it. &nbsp;This is intended for when you want to preserve a listing for later comparisons, and don’t want to accidentally write into it.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1569897201X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Get MACro Button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button will show the <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">File<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Open<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> dialog, where you can select a saved <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"macros.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">MACro<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> file, which then goes to the MACro editor. &nbsp;You can also use the <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"hidd_mwm.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">MWM<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> dialog for this purpose, or use the command <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">LM<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">filename<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1570230792="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Index command (Help menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to display the opening screen of Help. &nbsp;From the opening screen, you can jump to step-by-step instructions for using SYNOPSYS and various types of reference information.  <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Once you open Help, you can click the Contents button whenever you want to return to the opening screen.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1611663554="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Using Help command (Help menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command for instructions about using Help.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1601686837X="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Title Bar<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading2\"><img src=\"titlebar.png\" width=\"257\" height=\"31\" alt=\"titlebar\" style=\"width:257px;height:31px;border:none\"><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_Intro\" style=\"text-indent: -24px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Intro\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">The title bar is located along the top of a window. &nbsp;It contains the name of the application and lens name.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_Intro\" style=\"text-indent: -24px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><span class=\"f_Intro\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">To move the window, drag the title bar. &nbsp;Note: You can also move dialog boxes by dragging their title bars.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">A title bar may contain the following elements:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 3px 0px 3px 0px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:24px\"><img src=\"bullet.png\" width=\"6\" height=\"6\" alt=\"bullet\" style=\"width:6px;height:6px;border:none\"><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span class=\"f_Ln1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Application Control-menu button<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 3px 0px 3px 0px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:24px\"><img src=\"bullet.png\" width=\"6\" height=\"6\" alt=\"bullet\" style=\"width:6px;height:6px;border:none\"><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span class=\"f_Ln1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Document Control-menu button<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 3px 0px 3px 0px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:24px\"><img src=\"bullet.png\" width=\"6\" height=\"6\" alt=\"bullet\" style=\"width:6px;height:6px;border:none\"><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span class=\"f_Ln1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Maximize button<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 3px 0px 3px 0px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:24px\"><img src=\"bullet.png\" width=\"6\" height=\"6\" alt=\"bullet\" style=\"width:6px;height:6px;border:none\"><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span class=\"f_Ln1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Minimize button<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 3px 0px 3px 0px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:24px\"><img src=\"bullet.png\" width=\"6\" height=\"6\" alt=\"bullet\" style=\"width:6px;height:6px;border:none\"><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span class=\"f_Ln1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Name of the application<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 3px 0px 3px 0px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:24px\"><img src=\"bullet.png\" width=\"6\" height=\"6\" alt=\"bullet\" style=\"width:6px;height:6px;border:none\"><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span class=\"f_Ln1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Name of the lens<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 3px 0px 3px 0px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:24px\"><img src=\"bullet.png\" width=\"6\" height=\"6\" alt=\"bullet\" style=\"width:6px;height:6px;border:none\"><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span class=\"f_Ln1\" style=\"font-family: Arial;\">Restore button<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div>"
popid_1294918415="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">No Help Available<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">No help is available for this area of the window.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_789379287="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">KICK button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button will <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um1012.htm#kick\" class=\"topiclink\">KICK<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> the lens, sometimes jumping out of a local minimum and finding a better solution region.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1537088808X="<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Options<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Graphics<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Kill All Graphics Windows<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">Immediately closes all open graphics windows.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Command:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span style=\"width:48px\">&nbsp;<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">KAG<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Shortcut:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><img src=\"killallgraphics.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"killallgraphics\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><\/p>\n\r"
popid_433975737X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Last Menu<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button becomes active after you have opened one of the many interactive dialog windows and either ran a function there or closed the window. &nbsp;Immediately after closing the window, you can usually reopen it simply by pressing the &lt;Enter&gt; key, but if you have run any other commands in the meantime, that no longer works.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">That is the function of this button: it goes immediately back to the last-opened dialog.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">You can also do the same thing with the command<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">RTM.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_21406226="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Graphics Zoom To<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button becomes active only when you drag enclose a portion of the graphics display. &nbsp;It then zooms and pans the display to show that portion.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_21796549="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Load Line Buffer (LLB)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Selecting this item will load the last 20 commands that you typed into a MACro editor, where you may edit or save them, and run them again.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_838564254="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Load Menu into MACro<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Selecting this item will open the MACro LASTMENU.MAC, which contains a copy of the input that was generated by the last menu dialog that you ran. &nbsp;With this MACro you can easily run that sequence again without having to open the menu and fill in the data boxes all over again.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">You can also edit these data, and save the MACro with another name, making it permanent.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_78322916X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-weight: bold;\">Make new lens<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\">Selecting this option will erase any lens currently in effect and create a new lens with only a minimum of data. &nbsp;You can then add elements as you wish.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_362924725X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Execute MWM Command<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Click this button to bring up the MWM MACro selection dialog, where you may open edit, or delete a saved MACro.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_449885449X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-weight: bold;\">New pen width<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\">This dialog lets you select the width of the pen that will be used by the graphics features of SYNOPSYS when making printed hardcopy. &nbsp;There is very little difference in the screen display, but it is more evident on paper.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1250826645="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Nobeep button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Normally SYNOPSYS alerts you to an error condition with a beep from the CPU speaker. &nbsp;If this sound annoys you, you can turn off the beeper by clicking on this button. &nbsp;Be sure to check the error button just to the left; when it turns red it means you have an error message waiting. &nbsp;Click the red light to read your message.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\" style=\"text-indent: 48px;\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1251773666="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Erase MACro Name<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\">Clicking on this button will change the name of the current MACro to DEFAULT.MAC. &nbsp;This is useful when you want to change something but do not want to overwrite the current version.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_355947527="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-weight: bold;\">Error light reset<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\">This option resets the error light behavior, so that all errors that turn on the light will again do so.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1609809564="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">SketchPAD<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">LensEdit<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">clicking on the button <\/span><img src=\"le.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"le\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> opens an <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um1333.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">LE<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> lens-editing window, where you can make any change you want to the lens data. &nbsp;When your changes are done, click the button <\/span><img src=\"runmacro.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"runmacro\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> in the editor toolbar to process the changes and automatically update the SketchPAD display.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1915220258X="<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">PAD: Circled Surface Numbers<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>Click here to toggle the display of the circled surface numbers.<\/p>\n\r"
popid_1901779162X="<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Set PAD pen width<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>This menu item opens a dialog where you select from several pen widths. &nbsp;The PAD display does not change much except for the widest pen – but if you make a hardcopy of the display the change is more apparent. &nbsp;You must close and reopen the PAD display to see the change.<\/p>\n\r"
popid_177678057="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Zoom PAD to 1:1<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\">Clicking this button in the PAD toolbar will zoom and pan the display so that hardcopy prints will display the top drawing at the scale requested.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_50422491X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">PAD Zoom To<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button becomes active only when you drag enclose a portion of the PAD display. &nbsp;It then zooms and pans the display to show that portion.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_3714050="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Pad Rulers<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Click on this button to display horizontal and vertical rulers in the top portion of the PAD display. &nbsp;This must currently be a lens drawing, either paraxial, Y-Z profile, or perspective. &nbsp;The rulers are shown in the units of the lens file.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Each ruler comes equipped with two black boxes at the ends. &nbsp;These are <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-style: italic;\">handles<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> that you can click and drag to move or resize the rulers.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_146770617="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">PAD Stereo Display<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button converts the top display in PAD to a red-blue stereo pair, which can be seen in 3-D with the red-blue anaglyph glasses provided to each user when he registers.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1120115793X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">SketchPAD Switches<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking here will open a dialog showing the <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um29.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">mode switches<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> that affect the PAD display.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_34818073="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">PAD Y-YBAR diagram button:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Click this button to open the Y-YBAR diagram, where you may edit first-order properties of the lens.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_944890729X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-weight: bold;\">PON status<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\">This portion of the status bar displays the characters &quot;PON&quot; when the program is in print-capture mode. &nbsp;For more information see <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um1310.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">Section 13.10<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_249726312="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-weight: bold;\">Quiet Status<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\">This portion of the status bar shows whether SYNOPSYS is in quiet mode. &nbsp;You can enter this mode with the command QUIET, or by turning on switch 72. &nbsp;All output to the Command Window is suppressed in this mode, making some features execute more quickly. &nbsp;To resume sending output to the window, use the command LOUD or turn off switch 72.e sending output to the window, use the command LOUD or turn off switch 72.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1919883557="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">RPER DXF button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">After your <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um72.htm#rper\" class=\"topiclink\">RPER<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> drawing is displayed, click here to save the current view as a 3D DXF file. &nbsp;This file can be imported into many CAD programs, some of which may be able to rotate the drawing.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_950980421="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">RPER to IGES translation<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button codes the raw RPER data into a form that can be read by many commercial CAD programs, using the IGES format. &nbsp;The view angles in this file are always (0,0).<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_14274058="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">SAVE LOG button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">The button <\/span><img src=\"savelog.png\" width=\"25\" height=\"26\" alt=\"savelog\" style=\"width:25px;height:26px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> is intended to make it easy to keep track of your lenses and MACros. &nbsp;This button appears on both the main window toolbar and also on the MACro editor toolbar. &nbsp;Clicking the former saves the current lens as an .RLE file whose name is just the current log number. &nbsp;Clicking the latter saves the contents of the editor as a .MAC file with the same name. &nbsp;The new file name is assigned to the lens (which is the behavior of the SAVE LOG command) but not to the MACro. &nbsp;Thus, if your MACro had previously been named “MY_OPT.MAC”, it will retain the same name afterwards. &nbsp;(This is so that if you change the MACro and run it again, it will not overwrite the file that you saved with the log number as a name.)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">In order for this procedure to be useful, you should put a LOG command at the start of the optimization MACro. &nbsp;That way, every time it is run, the log number is incremented. &nbsp;Then, for example, when you have clicked this button in both places, you know that the optimization MACro that produced the lens named 1234.RLE has been saved as 1234.MAC.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r"
popid_625229266="<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Save MACro<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">Saves the current MACro with the current name. &nbsp;You do not ordinarily have to use this option, since <\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-style: italic;\">running <\/span><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">the MACro will save it first, and then run it.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_151792761="<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Save MACro As<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyTextIndent3\" style=\"text-indent: 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_BodyTextIndent3\">Opens the Windows File Save As dialog box, prompting for a filename. &nbsp;Click OK to save the MACro with the new name.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_16185459="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet: Checkpoint<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button <\/span><img src=\"checkpoint.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"checkpoint\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> saves the current lens as a checkpoint. &nbsp;A later Undo <\/span><img src=\"undo.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"undo\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> will revert to this configuration.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_386215209="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Close command (Control menus)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_List\"><span class=\"f_List\">Use this command to close the active window or dialog box.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_List\"><span class=\"f_List\">Double-clicking a Control-menu box is the same as choosing the Close command.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_List\"><img src=\"appexit.png\" width=\"98\" height=\"88\" alt=\"appexit\" style=\"width:98px;height:88px;border:none\"><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_List\"><span class=\"f_List\">Note: &nbsp;If you have multiple windows open, the Close command on the document Control menu closes only one window at a time.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Shortcuts<\/span><\/p>\n\r<div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">Keys: <\/span><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">CTRL+F4 closes a document window<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\"><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">ALT+F4 closes all windows and exits from SYNOPSYS<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span style=\"width:48px\">&nbsp;<\/span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<\/p>\n\r"
popid_2037290843="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Maximize command (System menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to enlarge the active window to fill the available space.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Shortcut<\/span><\/p>\n\r<div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">Mouse:<\/span><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">Click the maximize icon <\/span><img src=\"scmax.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"scmax\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\"> on the title bar; or double-click the title bar.<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">Keys:<\/span><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">CTRL+F10 enlarges a document window.<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><p style=\"text-indent: -24px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 72px;\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r"
popid_401496747X="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Minimize command (application Control menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to reduce the SYNOPSYSwindow to an icon.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Shortcut<\/span><\/p>\n\r<div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">Mouse:<\/span><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">Click the minimize icon <\/span><img src=\"scmin.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"scmin\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\"> on the title bar.<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border:none;border-spacing:0px;padding:0px;line-height: normal;\"><tr style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><td style=\"border:none;padding:0;width:72px\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">Keys:<\/span><\/td><td style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><span style=\"font-family: Helv;\">ALT+F9<\/span><\/td><\/tr><\/table><\/div><p style=\"text-indent: -24px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 72px;\">&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r"
popid_2007441860="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Move command (Control menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to display a four-headed arrow so you can move the active window or dialog box with the arrow keys.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_List\"><img src=\"curarw4.png\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" alt=\"curarw4\" style=\"width:28px;height:28px;border:none\"><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_List\"><span class=\"f_List\">Note: &nbsp;This command is unavailable if you maximize the window.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Shortcut<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading2\"><span class=\"f_heading2\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Keys: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;CTRL+F7<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_170149154="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Next Window command (document Control menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to switch to the next open window. &nbsp;SYNOPSYS determines which window is next according to the order in which you opened the windows.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Shortcut<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading2\"><span class=\"f_heading2\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Keys: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;CTRL+F6<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1138482782="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Previous Window command (document Control menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to switch to the previous open document window. &nbsp;SYNOPSYS determines which window is previous according to the order in which you opened the windows.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Shortcut<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading2\"><span class=\"f_heading2\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Keys: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;SHIFT+CTRL+F6<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_463231111="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Restore command (Control menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to return the active window to its size and position before you chose the Maximize or Minimize command.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_2007907980="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Size command (System menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to display a four-headed arrow so you can size the active window with the arrow keys.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading2\"><img src=\"curarw4.png\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" alt=\"curarw4\" style=\"width:28px;height:28px;border:none\"><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">After the pointer changes to the four-headed arrow:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_List\"><span class=\"f_List\">1. Press one of the DIRECTION keys (left, right, up, or down arrow key) to move the pointer to the border you want to move.  <\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_List\"><span class=\"f_List\">2. Press a DIRECTION key to move the border.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_List\"><span class=\"f_List\">3. Press ENTER when the window is the size you want.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Note: &nbsp;This command is unavailable if you maximize the window.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;\">Shortcut<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Mouse: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Drag the size bars at the corners or edges of the window.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1368772058="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Switch to command (application Control menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to display a list of all open applications. &nbsp;Use this “Task List” to switch to or close an application on the list.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Shortcut<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Keys: &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;CTRL+ESC<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Dialog Box Options<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">When you choose the Switch To command, you will be presented with a dialog box with the following options:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Task List<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Select the application you want to switch to or close.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Switch To<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Makes the selected application active.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">End Task<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Closes the selected application.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Cancel<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Closes the Task List box.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Cascade<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Arranges open applications so they overlap and you can see each title bar. &nbsp;This option does not affect applications reduced to icons.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Tile<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Arranges open applications into windows that do not overlap. &nbsp;This option does not affect applications reduced to icons. &nbsp;The TILE <\/span><span class=\"f_BodyText2\" style=\"font-style: italic;\">command<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyText2\"> arranges new graphics windows in a grid.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_heading1\"><span class=\"f_heading1\" style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Arrange Icons<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText2\"><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">Arranges the icons of all minimized applications across the bottom of the screen.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_760526793="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Graphics Plot Placement Button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button opens a dialog that lets you choose whether to make a hardcopy printout at full scale or &frac14; scale. &nbsp;In the latter case you can select where on the page the picture is to appear. &nbsp;With this feature you can put four plots on the same page, if your printer allows you to feed the same page in multiple times.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">The option to “Use Screen Scale” attempts to size the graphics to correspond to the current magnification in effect in the graphics window.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&quot;Plot Full Scale&quot; makes a hardcopy at full scale, ignoring the screen settings.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">There is also a command-mode way to position your graphics on a page. &nbsp;See <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um1314.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">Section 13.14<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_838577332="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">SPS button:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Click here to open the <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"hidd_sps2.htm#sps\" class=\"topiclink\">SPS<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> spreadsheet lens data editor. The spreadsheet lets you alter the lens by typing new data into rows and columns, and it can link to other dialogs where you can define the object and system data.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1128621319X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Stopsign<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Click the button <\/span><img src=\"clip0407.png\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" alt=\"clip0407\" style=\"width:28px;height:28px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> when you want to halt a process before it completes normally. &nbsp;Many of the more lengthy procedures, such as optimization, periodically check this button, and will end gracefully if it has been clicked, although it usually will not terminate instantly.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_151884691X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Stock Lenses Button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This button opens a dialog that can access the stock lens elements from eight different vendors. &nbsp;For more information, <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"hidd_vendors.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">click here<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_773198822X="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">View Menu<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">SideBar<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Click this menu item to toggle the <\/span><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"hidd_set_tb_action.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">SideBar<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_BodyText\"> button visible or hidden.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_811661102X="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">1, 2, ... command (Window menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">SYNOPSYS displays a list of currently open windows at the bottom of the Window menu. &nbsp;A check mark appears in front of the document name of the active window. &nbsp;Choose a window from this list to make it active.  <\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1527705571X="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Window Arrange Icons Command<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to arrange the icons for minimized windows at the bottom of the main window. &nbsp;If there is an open document window at the bottom of the main window, then some or all of the icons may not be visible because they will be underneath this document window.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_29496053="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Cascade command (Window menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to arrange multiple opened windows in an overlapped fashion. <\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_540183911X="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Tile command (Window menu)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Use this command to arrange multiple opened windows in a non-overlapped fashion.  <\/span><span class=\"f_BodyText2\">The TILE <\/span><span class=\"f_BodyText2\" style=\"font-style: italic;\">command<\/span><span class=\"f_BodyText2\"> arranges new graphics windows in a grid.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_60177909="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet Obscuration Options Dialog button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button opens the obscuration options dialog. When you click on a button in this dialog, you are prompted for the data that apply to that option.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_60177915="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet Outside Aperture Options Dialog button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button opens the aperture options dialog. When you click on a button in this dialog, you are prompted for the data that apply to that option.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_14523494X="<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Worksheet: Cement<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>When this button is clicked, you can then click on an airspace between two elements, and they will be converted into a cemented pair. &nbsp;The resulting buried surface will have the radius of the second of the two original surfaces.<\/p>\n\r"
popid_1947090307="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Worksheet: Double-Split Lens<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this tool, and then clicking inside a lens element, will insert two surfaces at that point, splitting the lens into two elements with a small airspace between..<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1707206590X="<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Pan Display<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>Click here, and then click and drag on the PAD display to pan the picture.<\/p>\n\r"
popid_1699410073="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Edit Lens ID<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Click this button to display a dialog where you may enter and edit the six lines of lens identification.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_378657860X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet Index Options Dialog button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button opens the index options dialog. When you click on a button in this dialog, you are prompted for the data that apply to that option.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1540946986X="<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet: Insert Prism<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p><img src=\"wsinsertprism.png\" width=\"24\" height=\"23\" alt=\"wsinsertprism\" style=\"width:24px;height:23px;border:none\"> This button is used to insert a prism from the prism library into the lens.<\/p>\n\r"
popid_365603756X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet: Flip Mirror<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Click here if you want to reverse the sign of the tilts on a fold mirror plus its associated dummy. &nbsp;Then click on the vertex of a fold mirror.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1739082425="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet: System Data<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button <\/span><img src=\"object.png\" width=\"26\" height=\"24\" alt=\"object\" style=\"width:26px;height:24px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> places the system and object data into the WorkSheet edit box.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1712014211X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet: Pupil Wizard<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>Clicking this button <img src=\"pwizard.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"26\" alt=\"pwizard\" style=\"width:30px;height:26px;border:none\"> opens the Pupil Wizard, where you may edit data defining the object point and the entrance pupil.<\/p>\n\r"
popid_60205639="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet Curvature Options Dialog button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button opens the curvature options dialog. &nbsp;When you click on a button in this dialog, you are prompted for the data that apply to that option.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_345756566X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Worksheet: Split Lens<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this tool, and then clicking inside a lens element, will insert a single surface at that point, splitting the lens into two elements in contact.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_60208535="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet SYS Dialog button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button opens the SYS dialog, where you can edit all of the system parameters.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1699410550="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet Thickness Options Dialog button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button opens the thickness options dialog. When you click on a button in this dialog, you are prompted for the data that apply to that option.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_341433152X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">WorkSheet Tilt and Decenter Options Dialog button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Clicking this button opens the tilt and decenter options dialog. When you click on a button in this dialog, you are prompted for the data that apply to that option.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_729384601X="<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Worksheet: Uncement<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>When this button is clicked, you can then click on the second element of a cemented pair and they will be converted into an airspaced pair. &nbsp;The thickness separating them will initially be zero, and you will have to set a reasonable value yourself.<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r"
popid_1705862230X="<p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Undo button:<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>Click here to go back to the latest checkpoint.<\/p>\n\r"
popid_1374834120X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Glass Data Dialog<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">The Glass Data dialog shows the glass attributes for a selected material, along with a graph of the material transmission. &nbsp;You can reach this dialog from PAD by clicking the button <\/span><img src=\"glasstable.png\" width=\"27\" height=\"25\" alt=\"glasstable\" style=\"width:27px;height:25px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">, and then by clicking on a glass symbol and then the Properties button, or else with the cursor selection <\/span><img src=\"gtpointer.png\" width=\"18\" height=\"18\" alt=\"GTpointer\" style=\"width:18px;height:18px;border:none\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">. &nbsp;Then just click on a glass symbol and the dialog appears. &nbsp;(Another feature lists glass attributes on the Command Window. &nbsp;See <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um525.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">Section 5.25<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">.) &nbsp;A sample is shown below.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><img src=\"gtbdschott.png\" width=\"736\" height=\"530\" alt=\"gtbdschott\" style=\"width:736px;height:530px;border:none\"><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">These data must be interpreted with caution. &nbsp;The optical glass manufacturers have not agreed on the definition or range of the environmental attributes such as acid sensitivity, etc., and the listed numbers therefore cannot be directly compared with those from a different vendor – although a low value means a more stable glass than does a high value, in any one catalog. &nbsp;The listed price is the ratio of the cost of the glass to that of glass type BK7; the value listed is not necessarily current, since vendors update their price list frequently.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">The displayed material transmission must be viewed as no more than a rough approximation showing the useful range of the material. &nbsp;The algorithm models transmission by interpolating between data points provided by a vendor, but in some cases the materials listed are available from a variety of vendors, and the properties of their product can differ from those of other vendors. &nbsp;You are therefore urged to consult the technical data provided by the vendor you plan to purchase from, if the exact transmission properties are critical to your project. &nbsp;A sample of one of the U materials is shown below.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><img src=\"gtbdunusual.png\" width=\"736\" height=\"532\" alt=\"gtbdunusual\" style=\"width:736px;height:532px;border:none\"><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">The listed data for materials in the U catalog show two different wavelength ranges. &nbsp;In the above example, the “Wavl. range “ tells you that the index data coefficients are valid over the range from 0.2 to 2.2 uM, while the “Transmission data range” says that the transmission function is valid from 0.3 to 2.0 uM. &nbsp;These two ranges are different for most of the materials, depending on what kind of curves the vendor has supplied.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1907477439X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Picture Box<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">The small lens drawing box that opens with some features lets you preview the lens and monitor your changes.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1439969889="<p><span class=\"f_footnotereference-2\"> <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Select Plot Placement<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>This dialog lets you decide where you want your hardcopy plotted output to be positioned on the page.  <\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<div style=\"text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px; margin: 0px 0px 0px 24px;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"4\" border=\"0\" style=\"border:none; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse;\">\n\r<tr style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\">\n\r<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:88px; padding:4px; border:solid 1px #000000;\"><p>Use Screen Scale<\/p>\n\r<\/td>\n\r<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:406px; padding:4px; border:solid 1px #000000;\"><p>Positions the plot on the page making allowance for the zoom and pan settings on the screen display.<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<\/td>\n\r<\/tr>\n\r<tr style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\">\n\r<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:88px; padding:4px; border:solid 1px #000000;\"><p>Plot Full Scale<\/p>\n\r<\/td>\n\r<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:406px; padding:4px; border:solid 1px #000000;\"><p>Makes a hardcopy printout at full scale, ignoring the screen settings.<\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<\/td>\n\r<\/tr>\n\r<tr style=\"text-align:left;vertical-align:top;\">\n\r<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:88px; padding:4px; border:solid 1px #000000;\"><p>Q1 … Q4<\/p>\n\r<\/td>\n\r<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:406px; padding:4px; border:solid 1px #000000;\"><p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">Reduces the plot size to &frac14; of the page and positions it in one of the four corners of the paper.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<\/td>\n\r<\/tr>\n\r<\/table>\n\r<\/div>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r"
popid_1108204414="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-weight: bold;\">Progress bar<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt;\">This display shows a progress bar to tell you how far along the program has gotten while performing a lengthy procedure.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1548639395X="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Save Lens As Dialog<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">This selection opens the Windows <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">File<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Save<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> dialog where you may enter the name of the lens file. &nbsp;You can also use the SYNOPSYS command <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">SAVE<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um372.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">filename<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"><a href=\"um372.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">. &nbsp;See also <\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um372.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">Section 3.7.2<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">.<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">When a lens has been saved to disk, it may be read back in with the command <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">FETCH<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">filename<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\">, or with the <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">MWL<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> dialog (or of course the <\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">File<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-family: \'Courier New\'; font-weight: bold;\">|<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Open<\/span><span class=\"f_footnotetext\"> dialog).<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_1500765605="<p class=\"p_footnotetext\"><span class=\"f_footnotetext\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Select file button<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>Clicking this button will open a dialog where you can select from a list of saved files. &nbsp;The top toolbar will open the MWL dialog, which is used for selecting a lens file. &nbsp;The EE editor toolbar will display a list of saved MACros, while the Graphics Window will display a list of saved SSP graphics files. <\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p>All of the above will display a preview of the contents of the file, making this option somewhat more friendly than the native Windows File Open dialog.<\/p>\n\r"
popid_378994841="<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Scroll bars<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_BodyText\"><span class=\"f_BodyText\">Displayed at the right and bottom edges of a window. &nbsp;The scroll boxes inside the scroll bars indicate your vertical and horizontal location in the window. &nbsp;You can use the mouse to scroll to other parts of the window.<\/span><\/p>\n\r"
popid_2995474="<p class=\"p_mine\" style=\"border-color: #000000; border-style: solid; border-width: 0px; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-left: none; margin: 0px 0px 1px 0px;\"><span class=\"f_mine\" style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">2.8 (Topic deleted) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<\/span><span class=\"f_mine\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um27.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">Previous<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_mine\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"> <\/span><span class=\"f_mine\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um29.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">Next<\/a><\/span><span class=\"f_mine\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"> <\/span><span class=\"f_mine\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um.htm#um_contents\" class=\"topiclink\">TOC<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_p2-10\"><span class=\"f_p2-10\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p class=\"p_mine\"><span class=\"f_mine\">(This section is currently unused.)<\/span><\/p>\n\r<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\r<p><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\">  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<\/span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um29.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">Next<\/a><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"> <\/span><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um27.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">P<\/a><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um27.htm\" class=\"topiclink\">revious<\/a><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\';\"> <\/span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"um.htm#um_contents\" class=\"topiclink\">TOC<\/a><\/span><\/p>\n\r"
